text: William Walker (born 31 October 1985) is a retired Australian professional road racing cyclist. He was born in Subiaco, Western Australia. He won a silver medal at the 2005 UCI World Championships. Walker retired in 2014 after having a case of ventricular tachycardia. ==References== Category:Australian cyclists Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Western Australia
